{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ff92c63b-418b-4931-9e5d-94f4300fbbfb","content":"No files found in the workspace — so here's exactly what to do in your existing project.\n\n## 1. Add `x:DataType` to SettingsPage.xaml\n\nAdd the `xmlns` for your ViewModel namespace and set `x:DataType` on the `ContentPage`:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Entry Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" Placeholder=\"Theme\" />\n\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n\n        <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"48\" />\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='Font size: {0}'}\" />\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThat's the only XAML change needed. The `x:DataType` directive tells the XAML compiler to resolve every `{Binding}` against `SettingsViewModel` at **compile time** instead of at runtime via reflection.\n\n## 2. Catch binding errors at build time\n\nCompiled bindings already emit **build errors** (not warnings) when a property name is misspelled or the type is wrong — e.g. `{Binding Themee}` will fail the build.\n\nTo make sure this is fully enforced, confirm your `.csproj` does **not** disable the source generator:\n\n```xml\n<!-- In your .csproj — these should be absent or true -->\n<EnableXamlC>true</EnableXamlC>          <!-- default is true -->\n```\n\nThen just build:\n\n```bash\ndotnet build\n```\n\nAny typo like `{Binding Themee}` will produce a compiler error such as:\n\n> **XC0045**: Property \"Themee\" not found on \"SettingsViewModel\"\n\n## Key points\n\n| Aspect | Interpreted binding | Compiled binding |\n|---|---|---|\n| Error detection | Runtime (silent fail) | **Build time** |\n| Performance | Reflection-based | Direct property access |\n| Required change | — | Add `x:DataType` |\n\n- `x:DataType` can be set on **any element**, not just the page root — useful when a child binds to a different type (e.g. inside a `DataTemplate`).\n- To **opt out** for one binding (e.g. a relative or ancestor binding), use `x:DataType=\"\"` locally.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5f8c0270-2864-4f4d-9ba4-6568e2a196aa","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty — there are no existing files. The user is asking a conceptual question about converting a MAUI page to compiled bindings. I'll provide the answer directly with examples.","outputTokens":718,"requestId":"1041:1F50C6:1540C97:17D2DEC:69FD3380"},"id":"9351215d-84e7-4364-9c92-59c3a329e11a","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:51:29.198Z","parentId":"14d621e6-eaa1-4904-9783-e37d09b13291"}
